                     <p class="ctpl-c-imagetext-container-right__para1">Pat is a Pregnant Parent experiencing severe morning sickness during pregnancy and uses two weeks of benefit allotment (2 weeks available for a serious health condition during pregnancy).</p>
            <p class="ctpl-c-imagetext-container-right__para1">Pat returns to work until the baby is born. After the birth, Pat uses 6 weeks of benefit allotment to recover from the birth. (6 weeks for pregnancy/childbirth).</p>
            <p class="ctpl-c-imagetext-container-right__para1">Pat returns to work. When the child is 6 months old, Pat elects to use the remaining 6 weeks of benefits to bond with the child. (6 weeks for bonding).</p>
